threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: This signature detects the presence of a number of Windows API functionality often seen within embedded executables. When this signature alerts on an executable, it is not an indication of malicious behavior. However, if seen firing in other file types, deeper investigation may be warranted.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: InQuest Labs

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a Go-based malicious utility, likely used for post-exploitation activities and lateral movement. The sample exhibits significant anti-forensic behavior, including the automated clearing of critical system logs (/var/log/auth.log, btmp, wtmp, lastlog) and the suppression of shell history (HISTFILE=/dev/null, HISTSIZE=0). It incorporates the 'golang.org/x/crypto/ssh' library and hardcoded command templates for automated SSH connections that bypass host key verification, suggesting automated lateral movement or brute-forcing. Furthermore, it contains functionality to archive and encrypt system data using 'tar' and 'openssl des3', which is indicative of data exfiltration preparation.
